<sn><md>## On Windows

1. Go to the official Git website: [https://git-scm.com/downloads](https://git-scm.com/downloads)
2. Download the **Windows installer**.
3. Run the installer and follow the setup wizard.

   * Accept the license.
   * Choose installation location.
   * Select default options unless you need specific settings.
4. Once completed, open **Command Prompt** and type `git --version` to confirm the installation.
</md></sn><sn><md>## On macOS

1. Open **Terminal**.
2. Run:

   ```bash
   git --version
   ```

   * If Git is not installed, macOS will prompt you to install **Xcode Command Line Tools**.
   * Follow the on-screen instructions.
3. Alternatively, you can install Git using **Homebrew** (if installed):

   ```bash
   brew install git
   ```
</md></sn><sn><md>## On Linux (Debian/Ubuntu)

Open the terminal and run:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git
```

For Fedora/CentOS:

```bash
sudo dnf install git
```
</md></sn><sn><md>## Verify Installation

Type:

```bash
git --version
```

If you see the version number, Git has been successfully installed and is ready to use.
